# Business Projects Rules

## General Guidelines
- Write professional, maintainable code
- Use clear variable and function names
- Comment business logic and data transformations
- Follow best practices for the chosen stack

## Code Style
- Keep functions focused and single-purpose
- Use consistent naming conventions
- Handle errors gracefully
- Write code that's easy to understand and modify

## Data & Security
- Never commit sensitive data (API keys, passwords, etc.)
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Validate and sanitize user inputs
- Follow data privacy best practices

## Project Structure
- Organize code by feature/component
- Separate business logic from presentation
- Keep configuration files organized

## Documentation
- Document API endpoints and data models
- Explain complex business logic
- Keep README files up to date
